Reasoning: The paper discusses burst identification in document streams and the use of mined burstiness information for an efficient document-search engine. This suggests that the paper is related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The use of spatiotemporal information also suggests that the paper may be related to spatial information systems (cs.SI) and deep learning (cs.DL). Finally, the use of datasets and experimental evaluation suggests that the paper may also be related to databases (cs.DB).
